Here are the top 3 deepest oceans in the world:

Pacific Ocean - The average depth of the Pacific Ocean is approximately 4,280 meters (14,040 feet), and it has the deepest point on Earth, the Challenger Deep, which has a depth of approximately 11,034 meters (36,200 feet).

Atlantic Ocean - The average depth of the Atlantic Ocean is approximately 3,646 meters (11,962 feet), and its deepest point is the Puerto Rico Trench, which has a depth of approximately 8,376 meters (27,480 feet).

Indian Ocean - The average depth of the Indian Ocean is approximately 3,872 meters (12,714 feet), and its deepest point is the Java Trench, which has a depth of approximately 7,725 meters (25,344 feet).